<html>
<head>
<title>HTML Menu with Key Board Shortcuts</title>
<style type='text/css'>
.clsAgOn  { width:125px; padding:2px; background-color:#c0c0c0; font-weight:bold; font-size:10px; font-family:Verdana; COLOR: #ffffff; }
.clsAgOff { width:125px; padding:2px; background-color:#FE8001; font-weight:bold; font-size:10px; font-family:Verdana; COLOR: #ffffff; }
</style>
<script language="javascript">
	function fnPopupPage(page) {
		var aH = 500;
		var aW = 400;
		var aTop = 20;
		var aLeft;
		if(screen.width)
		    aLeft = screen.width - aW - 10;
		else
		    aLeft = screen.availWidth - aW - 10;
		window.open(page, "_blank", ",height="+aH+",location=0,menubar=0,resizable=1,status=1,scrollbars=1,titlebar=0,toolbar=0,width="+aW+",top="+aTop+",left="+aLeft);	
	}
	function menuChanged(cbx) {
		var actionRedirect = cbx.value;
		if(actionRedirect!='') {
			if(actionRedirect.indexOf("js:")>=0) {
				eval(actionRedirect.substring(actionRedirect.indexOf("js:")+3,actionRedirect.length));
				cbx.selectedIndex=0;
			}
			else {
				window.location = actionRedirect;
			}
		}
	}
	function menuFocused(cbx) {
		cbx.className='clsAgOn';
		if(cbx.options.length==1)
			menuChanged(cbx);
	}
	function menuBlurred(cbx) {
		cbx.className='clsAgOff';
	}
</script>
</head>
<body>
	<div style='height:16px;background-color:#FE8001;vertical-align:absmiddle'>
		<select accesskey="F" onchange='menuChanged(this);' class='clsAgOff' onfocus='menuFocused(this);' onblur='menuBlurred(this);' onmouseover="this.className='clsAgOn';" onmouseout="this.className='clsAgOff';" id="Select1">
			<option value="">. File .</option>
			<option value="js:alert('Welcome to Community Script Center');">Welcome</option>
			<option value="http://www.microsoft.com/technet/scriptcenter/csc/default.mspx">Script Center</option>
			<option value="js:fnPopupPage('http://msdn.microsoft.com');">MSDN - Microsoft</option>
		</select><select accesskey="L" onchange='menuChanged(this);' class='clsAgOff' onfocus='menuFocused(this);' onblur='menuBlurred(this);' onmouseover="this.className='clsAgOn';" onmouseout="this.className='clsAgOff';" id="Select2" name="Select2">
			<option value="js:alert('Have a nice day. Good Bye.');">Log Off</option>
		</select>
	</div>
	<ol><b>About this menu:</b>
		<li>Works like a standard menu (i.e. like Notepad, Alt+F+S to save).  You can access these menu items in the same fashion i.e. Alt+F+M to access "MSDN - Microsoft"</li>
		<li>Use of SELECT element makes it to stay on TOP ALWAYS</li>
		<li>Menu items can open URLs as Popup</li>
		<li>Menu items can invoke javascript routines</li>
		<li>Easy to implement.</li>
		<li>The current version, does not support cascading menus.</li>
	</ol>
</body>
</html>